I&#39;m trying to transmit some data by CAN bus between two STM32 blue pill MCUs (STM32F103C8T6). The data array to be transmitted is composed by data read from other CAN bus devices, from ADC pins and from an accelerometer/gyroscope I2C module. At the transmitter, I can visualize all the data in the array right before being transmitted using a ST-link debugger. However, at the receptor, I receive all the data correct except for the accel/gyro module ones, that become just zeros.

I tried changing the position of the module data in the array, but still receive zeros at these positions. So, I decided to transmit just the accel/gyro data, but still receive zeros; if I add some dummy data in that array, I receive just the dummy data and zeros. I also tried changing the MCU of reception and turning the array into volatile or static, but nothing new happened. Moreover, I tried processing the data before transmitting, merging the bytes into 16 bit data, converting to float to some scale and finally reconverting into 8 bit data to the CAN bus, but didn&#39;t work.

The code below is for read the module; the data at position 0 is just dummy to know if the transmission was successful.

```
void MPU_Read(void){
	uint8_t add, accel_data[6], gyro_data[6];
	int i;
	
	add = ACCEL_XOUT_H;
	while(HAL_I2C_Master_Transmit(&amp;hi2c2, 0xD0, &amp;add, 1, 1000) != HAL_OK);
