The `%` operator for modulo is not supported in Oracle. You would need to use [function `mod()`](https://docs.oracle.com/cd/B19306_01/server.102/b14200/functions088.htm):

    select city,id from station where mod(id, 2) = 0;

**[Demo on DB Fiddle](https://dbfiddle.uk/?rdbms=oracle_18&amp;fiddle=6a68d837fbeb3e18cd2f42abdb50dcb4)**

